I'm an engineer, passionate about music and building technology for the future. I collaborate with and consult for startups and musicians alike - remote and/or in Boston.

Currently, I'm the CTO at Squarelink and the Blockchain Innovation Fellow at Harvard University. I focus on building tools to enable the mass adoption of blockchain.

As a musician, I produce indie, pop, and R&B artists in addition to performing live ‐ I play guitar, clarinet, and piano (amongst others). Check out some of my stuff on Soundcloud.

What's more interesting is combining the two passions. I previously started a company called Musical Minds ‐ brainwave-sensing headphones that help find music for you to focus, relax, get motivated, or reduce stress.

If you like what I'm doing or if you're interested in learning more, please Contact Me for collaborations or rates. You can also support me for as little as $1/month on Patreon.
